  sodium: 1290 mg
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @potatoes{16%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch pieces. Place in a #medium pot{} with enough
salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender,
~{10-15%minutes}. Reserve 1⁄2 cup potato cooking liquid, then drain.

Return potatoes to #pot{} and keep covered off heat until ready to mash in Step 6.

While potatoes cook, heat a #medium dry pan{} over medium-high heat. Add
@bacon{4%ounce}; cook, turning occasionally and adjusting heat if browning too
quickly, until crispy, ~{6-10%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a
paper-towel-lined plate. Wipe out pan.

Once cool enough to handle, roughly chop.

> TIP: If you added any other items to your meal (apps, sides, and/or dessert),
> you can get started on them now!

Meanwhile, trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary. Drain @corn{1%unit}; pat dry
with paper towels. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2%unit}, separating whites
from greens.

Toss green beans on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp}, @salt{},
and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for bacon over high heat. Add corn and cook,
stirring occasionally, until golden and lightly charred in spots,
~{4-6%minutes}. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #small bowl{}. Wipe out pan.

Once corn is done, pat @ranch steak{10%ounce} dry with paper towels and season
all over with salt and pepper. Heat pan used for corn over medium-high heat.
When hot, add a drizzle of oil. Add steak and cook to desired doneness,
~{3-6%minutes} per side. Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{}. Wash out
pan.

Melt @butter{4%tablespoon} in pan used for corn over medium heat. Add scallion
whites; cook, stirring, until softened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Sprinkle with
@flour{2%tablespoon} and stir vigorously to combine.

Whisk in @chicken stock concentrate{2%unit} and 1 cup water (2 cups for 4);
bring to a simmer and cook, whisking constantly, until thickened,
~{3-4%minutes}.

> TIP: If the gravy is too thick, add more water a splash at a time.

Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Use pan used for steak here.

To pot with potatoes, add one packet of @sour cream{4.5%tablespoon} and
@butter{4%tablespoon}. Mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth and creamy,
adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed. Season with salt and
pepper.

Serve mashed potatoes, bacon, green beans, corn, scallion greens, gravy,
@crispy fried onions{1%unit}, @white cheddar cheese{1/2%cup},
@truffle butter{2%tablespoon}, and remaining sour cream family style for everyone
to build their own mashed potato bowls.

Thinly slice steak against the grain. Serve alongside mashed potato bar.

> TIP: If you like truffle, feel free to swap in the truffle butter for the plain
> butter and skip serving it on the side!

> Bacon is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

> Steak is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.